We examined the effect of four siRNAs homologous to gag gene of FIV Petaluma FIV14 clone (G1, G2, G3, and G4) on the replication of FIV in CRFK/FIV cells. An siRNA homologous to firefly luciferase (Luc) was used as a control. RT activity in the culture supernatant 48 h after transfection was significantly (P
 < 0.05) reduced in the cells transfected with G1, G3 or G4-siRNA compared to those in mock-transfected and anti-Luc siRNA-transfected cells (Fig. 1
). Among the four anti-FIV siRNAs, G4-siRNA showed the strongest inhibitory effect on the replication of FIV.
